sec.p: Annual apparent survival of chats was not related to the average ENSO conditions experienced over the course of the year. The model that included the SOI MAY-APR term received less support than the model indicating that annual apparent survival was constant, and the beta estimate for the SOI MAY–APR term had 95% CI intervals that spanned zero (−0.28 ± 0.20, −0.68 to 0.12).
